      "Growing exceptional cannabis is equal parts science and intuition. At Frost, every plant begins its life in our propagation room, where carefully selected genetics are started from seed or clone. Seeds are germinated in a controlled environment with precise temperature and humidity, and within days, the first tap root emerges and anchors into a growing medium of coco coir and perlite. Clones, taken from our mother plants, are dipped in rooting hormone and placed under gentle lighting until they establish a healthy root system. This first stage is quiet and unhurried, setting the foundation for everything that follows.",
      "The vegetative stage is where the plant builds its architecture. Under eighteen hours of light, the young plants stretch and branch, developing the structure that will eventually support heavy flower production. Our cultivation team monitors each plant individually, adjusting nutrient solutions based on visual cues and runoff readings. We employ techniques like topping, where the main growth tip is removed to encourage lateral branching, and low-stress training, where branches are gently bent and tied to create an even canopy. This hands-on approach ensures that every plant receives maximum light penetration and airflow, reducing the risk of mold and promoting even development.",
      "When the plants are mature enough, we flip the light cycle to twelve hours on and twelve hours off, triggering the flowering stage. This is where the magic happens. Over the next eight to ten weeks, the plants redirect their energy from vegetative growth into flower production. Tiny white pistils emerge first, followed by the gradual swelling of calyxes and the development of resinous trichomes that glitter under the grow lights like fresh snow. Our team monitors trichome development under magnification, watching for the precise moment when the ratio of clear to milky to amber trichome heads indicates peak maturity.",
